这是个动词，对吧？

29
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:56,880
To spew.
喷出。

30
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:59,000
Well, what can spew?
嗯，什么能喷出？

31
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Volcano can spew.
火山能喷出。

32
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Exactly.
没错。

33
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,240
An engine can spew.
发动机能喷出。

34
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:03,440
A person can spew.
人能喷出。

35
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:04,440
Yeah.
嗯。

36
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:05,440
That's not very nice.
那不太雅观。

37
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:06,440
No.
不。

38
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:13,300
So basically it's to like expel or to shoot out from your mouth or something liquid.
所以基本上就是像从嘴里排出或喷出液体之类的东西。

39
00:01:13,300 --> 00:01:15,060
So in the case of a person, right?
所以对于人来说，对吧？

40
00:01:15,060 --> 00:01:18,800
So if a person spews, it means a person throws up, but it's usually very forceful.
如果一个人spew，意思是呕吐，但通常很猛烈。

41
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:19,800
All right.
好吧。

42
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:20,800
It's very messy.
很乱。

43
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:23,200
A volcano can spew lava.
火山能喷出熔岩。

44
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,200
Exactly.
没错。

45
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:26,800
So a volcano is spewing lava.
所以火山在喷出熔岩。

46
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:32,360
Now for the next word that we have, it's an informal way of saying that something is broken.
现在下一个词，是一种非正式的说法，表示某物坏了。

47
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:34,360
You could say it's busted.
你可以说它busted（坏了）。

48
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:35,360
It's busted.
它坏了。

49
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:36,720
My DVD player is busted.
我的DVD播放器坏了。

50
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:39,240
Man, my phone is busted.
天啊，我的手机坏了。

51
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:44,360
So it's an informal way, very popular, very common I would say, to describe that something
所以这是一种非正式的说法，很流行，很常见，用来描述某物

52
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:45,360
is not working.
不工作了。

53
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:48,880
I don't think many people actually say, well, it's broken or it's damaged.
我觉得很多人不会直接说，嗯，它坏了或受损了。

54
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:49,880
Yeah.
嗯。

55
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:53,840
They're pretty much mixed I think, but you will definitely hear busted if you're talking
它们可能混着用，但如果你和母语是英语的人说话，

56
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:54,840
to native English speakers.
你肯定会听到busted。

57
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:57,480
Or even like, for example, your arm.
或者甚至像，比如，你的胳膊。

58
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,800
He's got a busted arm.
他胳膊坏了。

59
00:01:58,800 --> 00:01:59,800
Exactly.
没错。

60
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:00,800
So busted.
所以busted。

61
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:01,800
All right.
好的。

62
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:03,720
